  "description": [
    "Page 8 THE KEY WEST CITIZEN Sunday October 22 W1 Gypsies Of Naval Air Take Training Devices To Scene By JOHN RIVERA SN and JOHN NELSON TDI Your first experience in the Navy F4D Skyray and youve already encountered trouble On your re turn to the airfield you notice that the malfunctioning of the aircraft is getting worse Its becoming harder for you to control the jet As you streak through the sky above the airfield your plane goes completely out of control You glance down as you fight with the controls and see the altimeter needle indicating your all too ra pid descent As you lose altitude the instru ments record wildly The runway is coming up at you at 600 mph In these last few seconds you know it is no longer possible to re gain control it is too late to eject As you feel it ready to hit the deck the freeze button is pressed You have just been through part of an Operational Flight Trainer OFT Hop That first experience was conducted in the cockpit of an F4D that never left the ground For the full story of this we bring in what we call"
